# Single source of truth for the XML bridge's PLATFORM-NEUTRAL native-image
# build args (GraalVM --initialize-at-run-time hints, JDK XML limits, etc.).
#
# Consumed by BOTH native build paths:
#   * bridges/xml/build-native.sh  (linux/docker musl-static) sources this file
#     and APPENDS the linux-only static args (--static,--libc=musl,...).
#   * scripts/xtask build_bridge_native() (windows/macos) reads this file and
#     exports it verbatim as QUARKUS_NATIVE_ADDITIONAL_BUILD_ARGS (neutral only;
#     musl/static must NOT reach windows/macos).
#
# Keep this the ONLY place native-image args live. application.yml intentionally
# does NOT set quarkus.native.additional-build-args: setting it in YAML *and*
# the env var makes SmallRye prioritize the indexed YAML form and silently drop
# the comma-form env-var args (the mislabeled-static bug).
#
# Format: a single comma-separated list on one logical line (Quarkus splits on
# commas). No spaces around commas.
NATIVE_BUILD_ARGS_NEUTRAL="-H:+AllowVMInspection,-Djdk.xml.entityExpansionLimit=64,-Djdk.xml.totalEntitySizeLimit=5000000,-Djdk.xml.maxGeneralEntitySizeLimit=100000,-Djdk.xml.elementAttributeLimit=10000,--initialize-at-run-time=net.sf.saxon.functions.hof.RandomNumberGenerator,--initialize-at-run-time=org.apache.hc.client5.http.impl.auth.NTLMEngineImpl,--initialize-at-run-time=org.xmlresolver"
